\begin_layout Subsubsection
Equilibrium Refinement (Cho-Kreps Intuitive Criterion)
\end_layout

\begin_layout Definition
Given a PBE in a signaling game, the signal 
\begin_inset Formula $s_{j}$
\end_inset

 is equilibrium dominated for type 
\begin_inset Formula $t_{i}\in T$
\end_inset

, where 
\begin_inset Formula $T$
\end_inset

 is a set of all types, if 
\begin_inset Formula $t_{i}$
\end_inset

's equilibrium payoff is greater than 
\begin_inset Formula $t_{i}$
\end_inset

's highest possible payoff from sending the signal 
\begin_inset Formula $s_{j}$
\end_inset

.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Given the definition of equilibrium dominance, we can define the following
 PBE refinement:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Definition
(Cho-Kreps Intuitive Criterion): If the information set following 
\begin_inset Formula $s_{j}$
\end_inset

is off the equilibrium path and it is equilibrium dominated for type 
\begin_inset Formula $t_{i}$
\end_inset

 then (if possible) the Receiver's belief 
\begin_inset Formula $\mu(t|s_{j})$
\end_inset

 should place zero probability on type 
\begin_inset Formula $t_{i}$
\end_inset

.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Let's consider pooling at 
\begin_inset Formula $e_{p}=0$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $w(e_{p})=9000$
\end_inset

.
 Therefore, the payoff to the low type at 
\begin_inset Formula $\left[e_{p},w(e_{p})\right]$
\end_inset

 is equal to 
\begin_inset Formula $u_{L}=9000$
\end_inset

, and the low types should never choose a level of 
\begin_inset Formula $e$
\end_inset

 such that: 
\begin_inset Formula \begin{eqnarray*}
u_{L}(e,w & = & 10000)<9000\Rightarrow\\
2e^{2} & > & 1000\Rightarrow e>22.4,\end{eqnarray*}

\end_inset

which ends up breaking all pooling equilibrium.
 Do you see why? Given the pooling equilibrium, the low type would never
 set her level of education greater than 22.4, which means that 
\begin_inset Formula $\mu(H|e>22.4)=1$
\end_inset

.
 Given these (even more refined) beliefs of the Receiver/employer, the high
 type employee/Sender would be better off by deviating to 
\begin_inset Formula $e=22.4+\epsilon$
\end_inset

