\begin_inset Formula \[
\mu(H|e)=\begin{cases}
\frac{8}{9}, & if\, e=e_{H}=e_{L,g}=47.1\\
0, & otherwise\end{cases}\]

\end_inset

which leads to the following (sequentially rational) wage schedule:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula \[
w(e)=\begin{cases}
9444, & if\, e=e_{H}=e_{L,g}=47.1\\
5000, & otherwise\end{cases}\]

\end_inset

In the solutions to part (d) above we found that the equilibrium 
\begin_inset Formula $[47.1,\,9444]$
\end_inset

 by finding where the low types were indifferent, and we know that the average
 productivity is 9444 when 
\begin_inset Formula $\frac{1}{2}$
\end_inset

 of the low types pool with the high types.
 
\end_layout

